      "writtenOn": "2019-03-20T18:41:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027d be better to use an inline script.  You should be able to pass whatever data is needed by the script either on the command line or via a temporary file (or even just by using a format string to include it directly into the script), and the results can be retrieved with either the raw_io or json modules.  Essentially, one of the command line arguments is a temporary file generated by the json module.  The script writes the file and the json module parses it as json and it\u0027s available as part of the step_result object.",
